  "text": "4 species (reviewed in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). Most of these inquiries have 70 primarily focused on testing the hypothesis that the ecotypes are local adapted, while little work 71 has been done to identify the causative selective agents (Wadgymar et al. 2017) . Typically, 72 studies of local adaptation have made use of field or laboratory findings and an understanding of 73 regional natural history to make predictions about potential selective agents, whether they be 74 herbivore resistance in aspect-specific stands of Quercus rubra [CITATION_3] ), winter 75 temperatures in natural populations of Arabidopsis thaliana (Ågren and Schemske 2012), or 76 predator avoidance via substrate crypsis in Chaetodipus intermedius [CITATION_4] . 77",
